---
description: Git operations must produce receipts. No force, no lies, no bypass.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git Discipline (hard rule)

Commit messages MUST begin with one of:
  CALORIE(scope): …   — value produced, gate passed
  CURE(scope): …      — deficit healed, typo/bug closed
  REFUSED(scope): …   — gate closed, change rejected (yes, REFUSED commits exist)
  BLOCKED(scope): …   — awaiting human gate, partial work committed

NEVER:
- Run `git push --force` or `--force-with-lease` without explicit user CALORIE.
- Run `git reset --hard`, `git clean -fdx`, or `git checkout -- .` without
  confirming with the user first. Destroying uncommitted work is REFUSED by default.
- Amend a signed commit without the user's explicit instruction.
- Touch `evidence/**` in a commit that is not itself an evidence receipt.
- Bypass the pre-commit hook via `--no-verify`. Ever. If the hook fails, the
  commit is REFUSED and the user decides.
- Commit `cell_identity.json`, `.env`, `~/.gaiaftcl/**`, or anything matching
  secp256k1 key material.

Branch naming:
  spike/<topic>     — exploratory, lives in a worktree
  fix/<scope>       — CURE in flight
  evidence/<id>     — IQ/OQ/PQ evidence in preparation

Never open a PR against `main` that is not squash-mergeable into a single
receipt commit.
